                                                                                                A relying party is an entity that relies on the certificate and the CA that issued the certificate
                                                                                                to verify the identity of the certificate owner and the validity of the public key, associated
                                                                                                algorithms, and any relevant parameters in the certificate, as well as the private-key
                                                                                                owner’s possession of the corresponding private key.
